text: Mo-sheung Grace Lau (born 19 October 1991) is a Hong Kong karateka. In 2018, she won one of the bronze medals in the women's kata event at the 2018 Asian Games held in Jakarta, Indonesia. Later that year, she also won one of the bronze medals in the women's kata event at the 2018 World Karate Championships held in Madrid, Spain. She is scheduled to represent Hong Kong in karate at the 2020 Summer Olympics in Tokyo, Japan.
